  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1256",
  "title": "Theming using CSS Modules",
  "body": "The current theming strategy in `react-instantsearch` is to have BEM CSS Classes but allow people to use any technique implemented by https://github.com/markdalgleish/react-themeable.\n1. Is this (BEM Classes) the right approach for a React based library?\n2. Should we use CSS Modules instead?\n\nhttps://github.com/css-modules/css-modules\nhttps://github.com/javivelasco/react-css-themr\nreact-toolbox allows them https://github.com/react-toolbox/react-toolbox#prerequisites\n\nI have 0 experience using CSS modules, but for sure we want to be compatible with them.\n\nAllowing other theming techniques is nice, especially if we are gonna wrap `react-instantsearch` in `instantsearch` v2\n",
